00:43:56.750 --> 00:44:00.760
You cannot scientifically
change someone's opinion.

00:44:00.760 --> 00:44:02.690
What you can change
scientifically

00:44:02.690 --> 00:44:04.900
is someone's behavior.

00:44:04.900 --> 00:44:08.150
The human mind has this
really interesting trait

00:44:08.150 --> 00:44:10.330
that we'd like to
think of ourselves

00:44:10.330 --> 00:44:12.327
as rational creatures,
but we're not.

00:44:12.327 --> 00:44:13.910
We have this
psychological trick where

00:44:13.910 --> 00:44:17.240
we decide how we want
to feel, and then

00:44:17.240 --> 00:44:20.800
our minds act like lawyers
and justify the thing

00:44:20.800 --> 00:44:23.340
that we want to believe.

00:44:23.340 --> 00:44:25.780
If you're a programmer, you've
learned to short circuit

00:44:25.780 --> 00:44:27.270
that to a certain extent.

00:44:27.270 --> 00:44:29.700
We tend to be very
logical creatures,

00:44:29.700 --> 00:44:32.375
but that is the
overall human tendency.

00:44:36.530 --> 00:44:38.290
You can't change
